description: Israel’s war on Gaza has become Palestine’s Liberation War. The brutality of the war and blatant disregard for international law have shaken global politics to the core. But with Arab unity, Palestine will win its liberation, paving the way to peace and security in the Middle East through a two-state solution.
title: How the Arab world will enable Palestine to win its war of liberation

description: TEHRAN - Iraqi President Abdul Latif Rashid has held a meeting with the acting Iranian President Mohammad Mokhber, saying that the most important achievement of late President Ebrahim Raisi was enhancing ties with neighbors.
title: Iraqi President meets Mokhber

description: TEHRAN – Leader of the Islamic Revolution Ayatollah Seyed Ali Khamenei held a meeting with the families of the late Iranian President Ebrahim Raisi and his companions who were martyred during a helicopter crash on May 19.
title: Loyalty par excellence

description: TEHRAN- Israel has scaled up brutal attacks in the Gaza Strip despite an order by the International Court of Justice directing the regime to halt its military operations in Rafah.
title: Israeli coup against international law

description:
TEHRAN - The Israeli occupation regime has been pounding the totally blockaded Gaza Strip for more than 230 consecutive days. 
Yet, Israeli warplanes and tanks committed more massacres against civilians on Saturday. It has also intensified its bombardment of Rafah in the southernmost part of the Strip.
title: Israeli army intensifies attacks on civilians

description: TEHRAN - Sobh-e-No investigated the sympathy of different countries of the world with Iran after the martyrdom of President Raisi and his entourage.
title: The power of Iran's foreign relations

description: TEHRAN - “Say, ‘Nothing will ever befall us except what Allah has destined for us. He is our Protector.’ So in Allah let the believers put their trust” (9:51).
title: A note on FM Amir Abdollahian: A man of battlefield and diplomacy

description: TEHRAN - Ali Bagheri Kani, the acting Foreign Minister of Iran, and Sergei Lavrov, the Russian Foreign Minister, held a phone call on Saturday, discussing the strengthening of cooperations.
title: Iran acting FM discusses bilateral relations with Lavrov

description: TEHRAN - A senior Iranian lawmaker has lauded the funeral of the late President Ebrahim Raisi, highlighting it as a powerful symbol of "national unity and solidarity."
title: MP hails funeral of late president as testament to 'national unity'

description: TEHRAN - The immense popularity of Hossein Amir Abdollahian is evident from the massive crowds that gathered to welcome his body and attend his funeral, as well as from the numerous ceremonies held in his honor across Iran, even in its most remote cities.
title: What made martyr Hossein Amir Abdollahian beloved among the people of the Region?

description: MADRID- Following the tragic accident that claimed the life of President Raisi and the other accompanying individuals, Article 131 of the Iranian Constitution was set in motion. According to this article, the first vice president, Mohammed Mokhber, was appointed by the Leader of the Islamic Revolution, Ali Khamenei, as interim president until the scheduled elections on June 28th.
title: Meet the new top officials of Iran

description: Tehran - Iran has voted for a United Nations General Assembly resolution designating July 11th as the International Day of Reflection and Commemoration of the 1995 Srebrenica Genocide.
title: Tehran backs UN recognition of International Day of Reflection for Srebrenica Genocide

description: TEHRAN - Iraqi President Abdul Latif Rashid, along with several former prime ministers, and the heads of several political parties arrived in Tehran on Saturday to offer condolences on the martyrdom of President Ebrahim Raisi to the Leader of the Islamic Revolution Ayatollah Seyyed Ali Khamenei.
title: Iraqi President in Iran to offer condolences over martyrdom of late Raisi

description: The UN's special rapporteur on Palestine on Saturday urged member states to impose sanctions on Israel along with an arms embargo until it stops "this madness."
title: UN rapporteur calls for sanctions on Israel

description: Hundreds of Japanese people organized a demonstration in front of the US embassy in Tokyo, to protest Washington's support for Israel and its supply of weapons that kill Palestinians in the Gaza Strip and the West Bank, according to "Russia Today".
title: Japanese protest in solidarity with Palestine

description: Deep political divisions in Israel over Hamas’ surprise military operation in southern Israel on October 7 have once again come to light as Transportation Minister Miri Regev and Army Chief of Staff Herzi Halevi have locked horns during a cabinet meeting.
title: Cabinet clash: Israeli officials spar over Hamas attack

description: Escalating violence in conflict-torn Myanmar’s Rakhine State has forced another 45,000 minority Rohingya to flee, the United Nations warned, amid allegations of beheadings, killings and burnings of property.
title: UN: 45,000 Rohingya fled fighting in Myanmar

description: The Israeli army arrested 180 displaced Palestinians from a school used as a shelter in the Jabalia refugee camp in the Gaza Strip, amid an ongoing military campaign in the camp, according to a prisoner group on Friday.
title: Israel arrests 180 displaced Palestinians

description: The number of people landing on England's southern beaches after making the dangerous Channel crossing fell by a third in 2023, but the latest numbers on a government website showed 10,170 arrived between January and May 25, up from 7,395 over the same period last year.
title: Over 10,000 reach UK on small boats

description: Waves swept away a section of the American floating pier installed to carry aid to Gaza, Israeli media reported Saturday.
title: Waves sweep away US-built floating pier in Gaza

description: TEHRAN – A number of female journalists from Latin America who took part in the first International Khorshid Media Festival held in Mashhad last year, have offered their condolences to the people of Iran for the martyrdom of President Ebrahim Raisi and Foreign Minister Hossein Amir Abdollahian.
title: Latin American journalists offer condolences for passing of President Raisi

description: The mother of Secretary-General of Lebanon's Hezbollah Sayyed Hassan Nasrallah has passed away.
title: Mother of Hezbollah chief passes away

description: TEHRAN-Three Iranian short films will compete in the 13th South Asian Film Festival of Montreal (SAFFM), due to be held from May 24 to June 2 in Montreal, Canada.
title: 3 Iranian short films to compete in South Asian Film Festival of Montreal

description: TEHRAN- Two new collections of selected poems by Syrian diplomat and poet Nizar Qabbani have recently published in Persian.
title: Two new collections of Nizar Qabbani's poems published in Persian

description: TEHRAN- The Director of the Swami Vivekananda Cultural Center (Indian Cultural Center) at the Embassy of India in Tehran has expressed great respect for Iran and the Persian language.

description: TEHRAN – The majestic site of Naqsh-e Rostam is undergoing significant landscape architecture enhancements to improve safety and the visitor experience.

title: SCO: Iran proposes visa-free travel among member states

title: Half-million-year-old evidence of human settlement found on the Iranian Plateau

description: TEHRAN – Iran lost to the Philippines 3-0 (25-16, 25-13, 25-15) in the 2024 AVC Challenge Cup for Women on Saturday.
title: Iran beaten by Philippines at 2024 AVC Challenge Cup for Women

description: TEHRAN – Iran Malaysia 7-1 in the 2024 Men's Indoor Hockey Asia Cup on Saturday to win the title for the ninth time.

description: TEHRAN - Italy defeated Iran 3-0 (25-19, 25-18, 25-11) in the 2024 Volleyball Nations League (VNL) in Brazil early Saturday.
title: Iran lose to Italy in 2024 VNL

description: TEHRAN –The sixth annual meeting of science attachés kicked off today in Tehran and is scheduled to conclude on Wednesday.
title: Annual meeting of science attachés kicks off

description: TEHRAN –Around 500 Persian medicine experts are providing health and medical treatment services across the country.
title: Some 500 Persian medicine experts working nationwide

description: TEHRAN –The second national exhibition on ‘Innovation for Prosperity’ will be held in Tehran from June 11 to 14.
title: Innovation for Prosperity exhibit slated for June

description: TEHRAN – The administration of the late President Ebrahim Raisi took different measures over the past three years to deal with air pollution in line with the Clean Air Law and climate change management program of the country.

title: 60,000 National Housing Movement units to be delivered to applicants in a week

title: Iran to use AI to improve electricity generation

description: TEHRAN – Iron ore production by Iran’s major mining companies increased by 38 percent in the first month of the current Iranian calendar year (March 19-April 19) compared to the same month in the previous year.
title: Monthly iron ore production rises 38% yr/yr

description: TEHRAN - Iranian Mines and Mining Industries Development and Renovation Organization (IMIDRO) and its subsidiaries have managed to indigenize the knowledge for the production of $838 million worth of mining equipment and machinery in the previous Iranian calendar year (ended on March 19).
title: Domestic production of mining equipment saves Iran $838m in a year
